article.headline: William & Mary beats Hampton 42-14
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. -- Mikal Abdul-Saboor ran for three touchdowns in William & Mary's 42-14 victory over Hampton on Saturday. Abdul-Saboor had 107 yards on 18 carries for the Tribe (1-1), scoring touchdowns from short range in the first, third and fourth quarters. Kendell Anderson scored two touchdowns and ran for 34 yards on eight carries. Steve Culley completed 9 of 16 passes for 135 yards. The Tribe led 20-0 at the break and never looked back. Leading 27-14 at the end of the third quarter, William & Mary would score twice more in the fourth on goal-line runs by Abdul-Saboor and Anderson. Hampton's first score of the game came on a 54-yard run by Christopher Dukes early in the third quarter. Five minutes later, Jaylian Williamson completed a 50-yard pass to Jorrian Washington for the second and final Hampton touchdown. Williamson finished the day with 335 yards passing for the Pirates (0-2).
